                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#iv #iir #iiv" facs="001 002">Fols. iv, iir, iiv</locus><title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2835RepCh119">Malkǝʾa
                                                  Mikāʾel</title>, incomplete at the beginning. Written in a different hand.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#186v #187r #187v #188r #188v #189r #189v #190r #190v #191r #191v #192r #192v" facs="189 190 191 192 193 194 195">Fols. 186v, 187r, 187v, 188r, 188v, 189r, 189v, 190r, 190v, 191r, 191v, 192r, 192v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2835RepCh119">Malkǝʾa
                                                  Mikāʾel</title>. Written in a different hand. Incipit:<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ምስለ፡ ስመ፡ ልዑል፡ ዘተሳተፈ።</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc>A bookmark made of parchment appears between <locus target="#37 #38" facs="040">fols. 37, 38</locus></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a3"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#1r" facs="003">f. 1r and passim</locus> mention the owner Wälättä Mädḫǝn, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a4"><desc><locus target="#7r and passim">Fols. 7r,, </locus> mention <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5226haylase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I</persName></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a5"><desc><locus target="#8v #96r" facs="011 098">Fols. 8v, 96r</locus>Prayer mentions Wäldä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, perhaps the late husband of the owner</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a6"><desc><locus target="#69v" facs="072">Fol. 69v</locus> mentions her father (without mentioning his name) and her mother Wälättä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a7"><desc><locus target="#96r" facs="098">Fol. 96r</locus> mentions her father Wäldä Ṣädǝq <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ጸድቅ፡</foreign>, her mother Wälättä Mikaʾel,  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, the soul of Wäldä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, and her children Gäbrä Waḥǝd, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ዋሕድ፡</foreign>, Säyfä Śǝllase, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰይፈ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>, Wäldä ʾAmanuʾel,
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ አማኑኤል፡</foreign>, ʾƎḫtä Mikaʾel, <foreign xml:lang="gez">እኅተ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, Ṣǝlalotä Dǝngǝl, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጽላሎተ፡ ድንግል፡</foreign>, Mǝśṭirä Śǝllase, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምሥጢረ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>. Cf. the list on <locus target="#185v" facs="188">185v</locus>, mentions the souls of Wäldä Mikaʾel,
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign> and Gäbrä Wäld, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ወልድ፡</foreign></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a8"><desc type="ScribalSignature"><locus target="#185v" facs="188">Fol. 185v</locus> mentions the scribe Zärʾä Yoḥännǝs <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘርአ፡ ዮሐንስ፡</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#">Fol. </locus> quires 2–7, 9–14, and 17–19.</desc></item>
